Global Process And Control Equipment Market Insights
Process And Control Equipment Market size was valued at USD 150 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 210 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 4.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Process And Control Equipment Market Overview
The global Process and Control Equipment market was valued at approximately USD 70.3 billion in 2024 and is projected to expand at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030. This growth is driven by the rising demand for automation across various industries, including oil and gas, chemicals, food and beverage, and pharmaceuticals. The increasing complexity of industrial processes and the growing emphasis on operational efficiency are key factors fueling the demand for process and control equipment. The market encompasses equipment used to control and monitor industrial processes to improve productivity, safety, and energy efficiency.

